d. Spiral galaxies have the wrong SEDs to\naccount for the excess. Future wide-field far-IR surveys using SIRTF and\nHerschel will sample representative volumes of the distant Universe, allowing\nany hot population of dusty AGNs and forming groups to be detected.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Feb 2002 17:45:34 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Apr 2002 16:49:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
