os (in particular [Si/Fe]dc and [Mn/Fe]dc)\ncloser to the solar values than Galactic stars. This could be explained by a\nlarger contribution of type Ia supernovae to the chemical enrichment of these\nDLA absorbers than in Galactic stars of similar metallicity. This metal-poor\nDLA absorber population could trace HI-rich dwarf galaxies. (Abridged)\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 Feb 2002 19:44:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
