{"id":"quant-ph/0202041","submitter":"Muhammet Ali Can","authors":"M. Ali Can, Alexander A. Klyachko, and Alexander S. Shumovsky","title":"Entanglement and the SU(2) phase states in atomic systems","comments":"10 pages, 1 figure","journal-ref":"PRA, 66, 022111 (2002)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.66.022111","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We show that a system of 2n identical two-level atoms interacting with n\ncavity photons manifests entanglement and that the set of entangled states\ncoincides with the so-called SU(2) phase states. In particular, violation of\nclassical realism in terms of the GHZ and GHSH conditions is proved. We discuss\na new property of entanglement expressed in terms of local measurements. We\nalso show that generation of entangled states in the atom-photon systems under\nconsideration strongly depends on the choice of initial conditions and that the\nparasitic influence of cavity detuning can be compensated through the use of\nKerr medium.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Feb 2002 15:26:49 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 24 May 2002 18:21:47 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Mon, 30 Sep 2002 11:47:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-07"}
